sor of German at Oberlin College.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aEnglish & American Literature. 4aGerman Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  a20th Century Literature.  aAlfred Döblin.  aBerlin Alexanderplatz.  aGerman-Jewish Writer.  aInternal Monologue.  aLiterary Montage.  aModernist Novelist.  aSocial Commentary.  aUrban Life.  aWeimar Republic.1 aBartscherer, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDollenmayer, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDollinger, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDollinger, Roland, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDonahue, Neil H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuesing, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDüsing, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFuechtner, Veronika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiesel, Helmuth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKleinschmidt, Erich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoepke, Wulf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoepke, Wulf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKrueger, Roberta L, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMueller-Salget, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller-Salget, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPfanner, Helmut F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSander, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabu